msIdentifier.repository: Library at the Herbert D. Katz Center for Advanced Judaic Studies

msContents.summary: Copy of the popular prayer book; the dual-page illuminated opening has headings as if for a Qurʼān (f. 1v-2r), but the text is Dalāʼil al-khayrāt.

title: Dalāʼil al-khayrāt wa-shawāriq al-anwār fī dhikr al-ṣalāh ʻalá al-Nabī al-mukhtār.

title.#text: دلائل الخيرات وشوارق الانوار في ذكر الصلوة على النبي المختار

name.#text: Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning

msItem.title: Dalāʼil al-khayrāt wa-shawāriq al-anwār fī dhikr al-ṣalāh ʻalá al-Nabī al-mukhtār.

supportDesc.extent: ii, 87, i leaves : 150 x 95 (90 x 50) mm bound to 150 x 100 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper center recto; catchwords every verso lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in revival naskh in black ink; pointed and vocalized.

decoNote: Dual-page illuminated first opening in gold with orange and pink flowers (f. 1v-2r); textblock border-ruled in gold; wide gold rules across the full page opening, or framing one side of a page-opening appear throughout the text, but not in the same pattern on each page; gold roundels with blue and orange dots punctuate the text; floral marginal medallions in blue and orange (f. 18v, for example); some pages are silver sprinkled; rubrications in red.

binding.p: Bound in reddish brown leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); embossed paper onlays of a central mandorla, two pendants on the vertical axis and cornerpieces; blind-tooled frame and lines connecting mandorla to frame; gilt-stamped floral medallion on flap.

origin.p: The copy was completed in the middle of Shaʻbān 1182 A.H. (December 1768); the scribe is not named.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by the Dropsie College for Hebrew and Cognate Learning (library bookplate inside front cover).
